  <static seed="651" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/QuadraticFunctions/QuadraticVertexForm10.pg">
    <statement><p>Write the vertex form for the quadratic function <m>f</m>, whose vertex is <m>(5,-6)</m> and has leading coefficient <m>a=-8</m>.</p>
<p><fillin characters="17" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>f\mathopen{}\left(x\right) = -8\mathopen{}\left(x-5\right)^{2}+-6</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>A quadratic function<rsq/>s vertex form looks like <m>f(x) = a(x-h)^2+k</m>, where <m>(h, k)</m> is the parabola<rsq/>s vertex.</p>
<p>The solution is <m>f(x) = -8(x-5)^2 - 6</m>.</p>
</solution>
